-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20pushed%20consumer%20prices%20higher%2C%26quot%3B%20analysts%2C%20including%20Aditya%20Bhave%2C%20managing%20director%20and%20senior%20US%20economist%20at%20the%20research%20unit%20of%20the%20banking%20giant%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20note%20on%20October%2031.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Trump%20unveiled%20his%20%26quot%3BLiberation%20Day%26quot%3B%20tariffs%20on%20April%202%2C%20while%20some%20trade%20deals%20have%20been%20negotiated%20with%20partners%2C%20such%20as%20the%20UK%20and%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20rates%20on%20other%20countries%2C%20like%20China%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-prime-minister-carney-apology-trump-tariffs-ad-canadian-reacttion-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECanada%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20remained%20elevated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20argued%20that%20tariffs%20would%20rebalance%20the%20trade%20deficit%20and%20bring%20billions%20of%20dollars%20back%20to%20the%20US%2C%20as%20Americans%20would%20be%20encouraged%20to%20shop%20domestically%2C%20and%20more%20manufacturing%20jobs%20would%20be%20introduced%20at%20home%20rather%20than%20companies%20relying%20on%20foreign%20labor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20many%20economists%20warned%20that%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20levies%20would%20be%20passed%20on%20to%20consumers.%20Research%20from%20S%26amp%3BP%20Global%20last%20month%20found%20that%20Trump's%20tariffs%20will%20cost%20businesses%20%241.2%20trillion%20this%20year%2C%20with%20shoppers%20ultimately%20bearing%20the%20brunt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20there%20is%20overwhelming%20evidence%20that%20tariffs%20have%20pushed%20inflation%20higher%20for%20consumers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20strategists%20said%20in%20the%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20wrote%20that%20they%20estimate%20tariffs%20to%20account%20for%20between%2030%20and%2050%20basis%20points%20of%20the%20core%20personal%20consumption%20expenditure%20inflation%20rate%2C%20which%20